	  <div id="main">	
	  	<div id="stream" class="container" data-intro='The story of the Boston Marathon Tragedy is colored in blue. You can see that the story is immensely popular on the first Monday, since that is when the two bombs went off killing two people and injuring many more. There was another large spike in the story on Thursday and Friday when the two suspects, the Tsarnaev brothers, shot and killed a policeman and were pursued by police until Friday evening when the only living suspect was captured.' data-step='2'>
	  	</div>
      <div class="middle-area" data-intro='Welcome to our Hacker News Visualization! We have broken up the news stories over the past two weeks into distinct themes that you can interact with. You can select the different themes by selecting these buttons or by clicking on the stream graph above. In the stream graph you can see the relative popularity of these themes over time. If you click on a specific theme in the graph, the other graphs will update their displays based on the selected theme. You can also create a custom theme with personalized keywords by selecting the &quot;Custom&quot; button.' data-step='1'>
        <h4 class='themes_heading'></h4>
        <button class="btn color1 selected premade" data-topic='0'>Boston Bombings
        <button class="btn color2 premade" data-topic='1'>Google Glass
        <button class="btn color3 premade" data-topic='2'>Cispa
        <button class="btn color4 premade" data-topic='3'>Startups
        <button class="btn color5 premade" data-topic='4'>Mobile
